				<outline text="A website from his home state commemorates Ted Belcher.

https://t.co/ddqLJ62zMh https://t.co/wQmGXBzrhw" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 17:25:51 GMT" tweetId="1410288483579699205" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1410288483579699205" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
				<outline text="Old blog post:

Twitter sort of relentlessly says, &quot;You will not shape anything but an endless, ever-vanishing flow of your tweets in our space. On our terms, not yours. With our goals in mind, not yours.&quot;" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 17:02:58 GMT" tweetId="1410282727761448962" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1410282727761448962" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
				<outline text="A friend of mine, who was there, finds that day pretty hard to talk about. https://t.co/SvkD4ELukZ" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 16:10:09 GMT" tweetId="1410269435852734468" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1410269435852734468" tweetUserName="KenSmith" >
					<outline text="But sometimes he gives me clues... https://t.co/S3tkTXDpJ4" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 16:10:10 GMT" tweetId="1410269437211590663" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1410269437211590663" inReplyToId="1410269435852734468" tweetUserName="KenSmith" >
						<outline text="And sometimes I guess what it all implies about we who sent them... https://t.co/TLTm4BLLGs" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 16:10:10 GMT" tweetId="1410269438964867072" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1410269438964867072" inReplyToId="1410269437211590663" tweetUserName="KenSmith" >
							<outline text="If they're going to go there in our name, the least we owe is our reflection... https://t.co/bFjRX69BRN" type="tweet" created="Wed, 30 Jun 2021 16:10:10 GMT" tweetId="1410269440625811460" urltweet="https://twitter.com/KenSmith/status/1410269440625811460" inReplyToId="1410269438964867072" tweetUserName="KenSmith" />
